node.text: Now here’s an absolute monster of a wave from @afonsobandagarra that is oh so worthy of recognition. Speaking of which, @nicvonrupp and his company @thebrusco have launched their #bruscochargerofthemonth comp, awarding the winner with a pack of surf goodies. “Our whole idea was to give credit and recognition to those underground chargers that constantly search for the best and heaviest waves in the Atlantic Ocean,” said Nic. “We want to inspire people to push their limits and there is no better example than these guys that put their lives on the line only for the pure love of surfing. This inspires me everyday and I believe it will also inspire the younger generations.” We couldn’t have said it better. Head over to the site for a full run down of this session and some insight from Afonso. Vid @vanlife_productions

node.text: Time for a 2-5 minute edit? Think most of us have these days. Every Friday, we'll be dropping one of our exclusive edits striaght to IG. First up, this session from deepest Cornwall in February of last year. The day before, the south west had been dripped by a blizzard, freezing over the roads and making travel damn near impossible. But a lucky crew managed to make the journey, hinderance free, and were greeted by a few barrels off this reefbreak. Featuring @alan_stokes @skindoggydog and many more, all shot by @biskit_bodyboarding you can find the full feature on the site, just search Cornwall in our shiny new nav bar.

node.text: Somewhere between Tijuana and Cabo San Lucas there’s a little corner of reef that holds sand in place—that turns lines into boxes, swell lines into slabs. It’s far from anywhere you’ve ever heard of and nowhere close to perfect, with a borderline impossible entry and a tricky doggy door exit, but there’s never anyone or anything there except coyotes and road runners, lizards and snakes, osprey and fish and dolphins and whales. node.text: In 2019, big wave hellman @marcelolunaoficial went mysteriously silent, and no one heard much of anything out of him. As it turns out, Marcelo suffered a number of potentially career-ending injuries and has been holed up at home, rehabbing, healing, and chomping at the bit to get back out there. Then in May this year, when one of Brazil’s newly hyped monster slabs woke up for the first time in a few years, Marcelo made his comeback official, whipping a beast and shrugging off a severe beating as it were nothing. Hit the link in bio for the full story. Pics by @luisreis_photo

node.text: There are few people who graft as hard as lensman @miahklein. No matter the scenario, this is a surf photographer who will always be in the right place at exactly the right time – and he's been doing just that for the better part of two decades. And that's not all. You see, Miah's as humble as they come, with an uncanny ability to truly listen and engage, to take in everything you're talking about and see all angles with refreshing positivity – a trait that's as engrained in his personality as it is in his camera work. Hit the link in bio.

node.text: EU hurricane strike? We can dream. But see Tropical Storm Larry off the Americas? It could become a hurricane soon and then recurve towards Europe. It's a long way out yet that this might hit - towards the end of the next week - but we think it's worth at least getting on your radar now and keeping an eye on it as it plays out. Full story, link in bio. - EDIT: Larry is now officially a hurricane.
